CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 23, 1951, pg. 6 reads: "Contestants - The six college students pictured above are among the nine students who are vying for scholarships from the Metoka Club. Winners of the contest will be announced at the annual garden party sponsored by Metoka Club on July 19. Lower row:..James H. Moone..."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of James H. Moone wearing dark bow tie and light colored suit jacket with dark handkerchief in left breast pocket, seated on bench in front of light colored background in Harris Studio
